{"title_page": "2017 Minnesota Golden Gophers football team", "text_new": "{{short description|American college football season}}\n{{Infobox NCAA team season\n|year = 2017\n|team = Minnesota Golden Gophers\n|sport = football\n|logo = Minnesota Golden Gophers logo.svg\n|logo_size = 125\n|logo_alt = \n|conference = Big Ten Conference\n|division = West Division\n|short_conf = Big Ten\n|CoachRank = \n|APRank = \n|CFPRank = \n|record = 5\u20137\n|conf_record = 2\u20137\n|head_coach = [[P. J. Fleck]]\n|hc_year= 1st\n|off_coach = [[Kirk Ciarrocca]]\n|oc_year = 1st\n|def_coach = [[Robb Smith]]\n|dc_year= 1st\n|off_scheme = \n|def_scheme = \n|stadium = [[TCF Bank Stadium]]<br>(Capacity: 50,805)\n|champion =\n|bowl = \n|bowl_result = \n}}\n{{2017 Big Ten football standings}}\nThe '''2017 Minnesota Golden Gophers football team''' represented the [[University of Minnesota]] during the [[2017 NCAA Division I FBS football season]]. The Gophers were led by first-year head coach [[P.J. Fleck]] and played their home games at [[TCF Bank Stadium]] in [[Minneapolis, Minnesota]]. Minnesota competed as a member of the West Division of the [[Big Ten Conference]]. They finished the season 5\u20137, 2\u20137 in Big Ten play to finish in sixth place in the West Division.\n\n==Recruiting==\n\n===Position key===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n|[[Running back|Back]]\n|'''B'''\n|rowSpan=\"6\" style=\"background-color:lightgrey;\"|\n|[[Center (American football)|Center]]\n|'''C'''\n|rowSpan=\"6\" style=\"background-color:lightgrey;\"|\n|[[Cornerback]]\n|'''CB'''\n|rowSpan=\"6\" style=\"background-color:lightgrey;\"|\n|[[Defensive back]]\n|'''DB'''\n|-\n|[[Defensive end]]\n|'''DE'''\n|[[Defensive lineman]]\n|'''DL'''\n|[[Defensive tackle]]\n|'''DT'''\n|[[End (American football)|End]]\n|'''E'''\n|-\n|[[Fullback (American football)|Fullback]]\n|'''FB'''\n|[[Guard (American football)|Guard]]\n|'''G'''\n|[[Halfback (American football)|Halfback]]\n|'''HB'''\n|[[Placekicker|Kicker]]\n|'''K'''\n|-\n|[[Kick