merican Conference|MAC]] and against [[Middle Tennessee Blue Raiders football|Middle Tennessee]] from [[Conference USA]]; the Gophers played on the road against [[Oregon State Beavers football|Oregon State]] from the [[Pac-12 Conference|Pac-12]].\n\nThe Gophers played nine conference games; they hosted [[Maryland Terrapins football|Maryland]], [[Michigan State Spartans football|Michigan State]], [[Illinois Fighting Illini football|Illinois]], [[Nebraska Cornhuskers football|Nebraska]], and [[Wisconsin Badgers football|Wisconsin]]. They traveled to [[Purdue Boilermakers football|Purdue]], [[Iowa Hawkeyes football|Iowa]], and [[Michigan Wolverines football|Michigan]], and [[Northwestern Wildcats football|Northwestern]].\n\n{{CFB schedule\n| rankyear = 2017\n| poll = AP\n| timezone = Central\n\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = {{tooltip|August 31|Thursday}}\n| time = 6:00 p.m.\n| w/l = w\n| nonconf = y\n| opponent = [[2017 Buffalo Bulls football team|Buffalo]]\n| site_stadium = [[TCF Bank Stadium]]\n| site_cityst = [[Minneapolis|Minneapolis, MN]]\n| tv = [[Big Ten Network|BTN]]\n| score = 17\u20137\n| attend = 43,224\n}}\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = September 9\n| time = 9:00 p.m.\n| w/l = w\n| nonconf = y\n| away = y\n| opponent = [[2017 Oregon State Beavers football team|Oregon State]]\n| site_stadium = [[Reser Stadium]]\n| site_cityst = [[Corvallis, Oregon|Corvallis, OR]]\n| tv = [[Fox College Football|FS1]]\n| score = 48\u201314\n| attend = 35,206\n}}\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = September 16\n| time = 2:30 p.m.\n| w/l = w\n| nonconf = y\n| opponent = [[2017 Middle Tennessee Blue Raiders football team|Middle Tennessee]]\n| site_stadium = TCF Bank Stadium\n| site_cityst = Minneapolis, MN\n| tv = BTN\n| score = 34\u20133\n| attend = 43,727\n}}\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = September 30\n| time = 11:00 a.m.\n| w/l = l\n| opponent = [[2017 Maryland Terrapins football team|Maryland]]\n| site_stadium = TCF Bank Stadium\n| site_cityst = Minneapolis, MN\n| tv = F