8580}}\n* \u201c[[Lead-Acid Battery]] Techniques for Bonding the Positive Plates,\u201d Vol. 49, N\u00b0 7, September 1, 1970, pps.&nbsp;1419\u20131446 {{OCLC|4433598564}}\n{{ref end}}\n<!--------------------------------------------------------------------------->\n<hr style=\"color:#A9A9A9;width:20em\" />\n{{ref begin|100em}}\n; ''[[EDN (magazine)|EDN]] (formerly ''Electronic Design News)'' \u2014 {{ISSN|0012-7515}}\n{{ref end}}\n{{ref begin|50em}}\n* \u201cPrinted-Circuit Packaging: Can It Be Carried Further?\u201d Vol. 10, N\u00b0 9, April 26, 1962, pps.&nbsp;38\u201351\n* \u201cHybrid Computation Gets Analog Out of Rut,\u201d Vol. 10, N\u00b0 21, October 11, 1962, pps.&nbsp;55\u201369\n* \u201cHeat and Pressure \u2014 A Way to Better Bonds, Part I:\u201d January 1967; \u201cPart II\u201d February 1967\n* \u201c[[Hall Effect]] Put in [[Integrated circuit|IC]],\u201d November 11, 1968, pg. 87\n* \u201c[[Schottky diode]]s Speed Up Digital [[Integrated circuit|IC's]],\u201d January 1, 1969, pps.&nbsp;37\u201340\n* \u201cTransistor Responds to Magnetic Fields,\u201d February 15, 1969, pps.&nbsp;73\u201378\n* \u201cReal-Time, Two-Way Communications Between Citizens and Leaders,\u201d June 1, 1969, pps.&nbsp;28, 112, and 113\n* \u201cGHz [[Amplifier]]s, Now They Are Practical,\u201d Vol. 15, N\u00b0 2, September 1970, pg. 41\n* \u201c[[Spinel]] May Make [[MOSFET#Metal\u2013oxide\u2013semiconductor_structure|MOS]] Faster Than [[Transistor\u2013transistor logic|T<sup>2</sup>L]],\u201d January 15, 1971, pg. 35 {{OCLC|4926284431}}\n* \u201c[[Digital Cassettes]] \u2014 Growing Like Wonderful Weeds,\u201d Vol. 17, February 1972, pps.&nbsp;28\u201335\n; March 1971 \u2014 ''EDN'' renamed ''EDN/EEE''\n* \u201cDigital Cartridges \u2014 New steps in Right Direction,\u201d April 1972, pps.&nbsp;26\u201329\n* \u201cCMSO Finally Gets It All Together,\u201d June 15, 1972 {{OCLC|4926524909}}\n* \u201cUsing [[Computer Aided Design]] to Talk to Machines in the Factory,\u201d August 15, 